On Nov 6, 2004, at 5:29 AM, Wayne wrote:

> Has anyone seen an oil drain plug that had an allen wrench hole in it? 
>  Any
> thoughts how to get my out so that I can put in a "proper" plug in so 
> that
> during future oil changes I can get it out with an opened-ended or 
> box-ended
> wrench?

That is the proper plug for a '79 :-)  I think some '78s have that 
style of plug, as well.

Just get a socket with the proper allen key on it, and use a ratchet to 
loosen it.

